# Zeno Classic Launcher — AI Workflow Rules

## 1. NEVER USE WORKTREES
- Never use `git worktree` or any isolated/worktree mode.
- Always work directly in the main repo directory.

## 2. AFTER EVERY CODE CHANGE — MANDATORY WORKFLOW

Complete all steps in order. Never skip.

### Step 1 — Full Release Build
Always run the FULL assembleRelease. Never partial builds for device testing.

```bash
export JAVA_HOME="/Applications/Android Studio.app/Contents/jbr/Contents/Home"
./gradlew assembleRelease --no-daemon
```

APK location: `app/build/outputs/apk/release/Zeno Classic.apk`

Or use the helper script (build + install in one command):
```bash
./scripts/build-install.sh
```

### Step 2 — Install on Device
```bash
adb install -r "app/build/outputs/apk/release/Zeno Classic.apk"
```

### Step 3 — Ask User to Test
After install say: "App installed. Please test it — does everything work correctly?"
Wait for response. Do NOT commit yet.

### Step 4 — Commit Only After User Confirms
Only if user confirms it works:
```bash
git add <specific changed files>   # never git add . or git add -A
git commit -m "description"
```
If user says it doesn't work — fix and repeat from Step 1.

### Step 5 — Push Reminder
After every commit check: `git rev-list --count @{u}..HEAD`
- **< 5 ahead**: stay local, do not push
- **≥ 5 ahead**: tell user "You have N commits ahead of remote. Want me to push?"

## 3. BUILD RULES

| | |
|---|---|
| Always use | `./gradlew assembleRelease --no-daemon` |
| Never use for device testing | `assembleDebug`, `compileReleaseKotlin`, partial tasks |
| JAVA_HOME | `/Applications/Android Studio.app/Contents/jbr/Contents/Home` |
| Signing | Requires `key.properties` at repo root |

## 4. GIT RULES
- Never commit before building + installing on device
- Never commit before user confirms the build works
- Never use `git add .` or `git add -A`
- Never force-push to `main`
- Never skip hooks (`--no-verify`)
